When making changes to issues we get bombarded with email announcing the notifications that were made.  My thought on the matter is, if I am the one that made the modification, why should I have to be notified? Notifications make sense for when someone else has made a notification, not for when I make a notification. If I make a change to an issue in which I am not the creator/watching it I don't get notified, this practice seems correct. So the issue seems to be that if I created/watch the issue I get notified of every change regardless if I made the change or someone else did. I purpose that a change be made so that regardless of your notification settings, you do not get notified of changes made by yourself.

