A NullPointerException is raised if a username passed to JiraWebActionSupport.getUserFullName() is non-existent.

This is the source code of the method:
{code}
    public String getUserFullName(String username)
    {
        User user = getUserManager().getUser(username);
        if (username == null)
        {
            log.warn("Could not retrieve full name for user '" + username + "'! User does not exist!");
            return username;
        }
        return user.getDisplayName();
    }
{code}

Obviously, line 4 should read "{{if (user == null)}}".

Also, I would recommend adding another check as a first line: "{{if (username == null) return null;}}"

h3. Issue Summary
Format of Wiki renderer fields in HTML Emails for updates is wrong

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create an Issue with this description:
{code}
{quote}
	h5. getting an Exception when trying to search  for "*+Gift certificate number+*"  in BO
{quote}
*+How to reproduce?+*
{quote}
#	In BO go to order Tab | Extras | Gift certificate number .
#       Click "*+search Button+*" 
#       now in the Filter choose "*+Gift certificate number+*" + "*+Is+*"   (eg. QFP5NLEUW45DTAUX).
#       when get the Msg Box "Not found " press "Ok" .(see attachment)
{quote}
{code}
# Enable email to yourself and HTML for the current user
# Edit Issue and change the line 
{code}
when get the Msg Box "Not found " press "Ok" .(see attachment)
{code}
to
{code}
when you get the Msg Box "Not found " press "Ok" .(see attachment)
{code}

h3. Expected Results
An email notification is sent, showing what changed, with the HTML/Visual format intact.

h3. Actual Results
A notification is is sent showing the wiki markup instead of the visual format:  !wrong_format.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Workaround
Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available
